        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45987",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "bq. ZendX_JQuery_Form_Decorator_UiWidgetElement does not set translator in its render() method.\r\n\r\nDecorator should not be aware of translator or translations and nor is {{Zend_Dojo_Form_Decorator_DijitElement::render()}}, which is equivalent with {{ZendX_JQuery_Form_Decorator_UiWidgetElement::render()}}.\r\n\r\nbq. Similarly ZendX_JQuery_View_Helper_UiWidget does not implement translation since it is deriving directly from Zend_View_Helper_HtmlElement instead of Zend_View_Helper_FormElement.\r\n\r\n{{ZendX_JQuery}}'s UiWidget view helper is extended similarly than {{Zend_Dojo}}'s Dijit view helper so I guess that the problem is not in view helpers neither.\r\n\r\nCould you provide some more info or code which details the problem.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-04-23T11:47:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-04-23T11:47:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46537",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wrobel",
                        "name": "wrobel",
                        "displayName": "Przemys?aw Wr\u00f3bel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "> Decorator should not be aware of translator or translations and nor is Zend_Dojo_Form_Decorator_DijitElement::render(), which is equivalent with ZendX_JQuery_Form_Decorator_UiWidgetElement::render().\r\n\r\nBut Zend_Form_Decorator_ViewHelper is aware of translator - see lines 242:244\r\n        $helperObject  = $view->getHelper($helper);\r\n        if (method_exists($helperObject, 'setTranslator')) {\r\n            $helperObject->setTranslator($element->getTranslator());\r\n        }\r\n\r\nand this allows view helpers deriving from Zend_View_Helper_FormElement to translate something when rendering...\r\nother examples are: Zend_View_Helper_FormElement, Zend_View_Helper_FormSelect, Zend_View_Helper_HeadTitle\r\n\r\nMy problem is that I am writing a from element + view helper for a jQuery plugin and I would like to translate something during rendering like other non-jquery view helpers can.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wrobel",
                        "name": "wrobel",
                        "displayName": "Przemys?aw Wr\u00f3bel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-05-11T15:03:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-05-11T15:03:29.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
